                <h1>Common Causes of Dishonorable Discharge Explained</h1>
                <p>Dishonorable discharge from military service often stems from severe misconduct, including criminal activity, substance abuse, or insubordination. Other reasons may include repeated violations of military regulations,Absent Without Leave (AWOL) issues, or fraud. Such discharges have lasting impacts on veterans' benefits and future employment opportunities.</p>
